The paper deals with modeling and predicting the quality of experience (QoE) of streaming video users using a recurrent neural network approach. This involves analyzing complex temporal dependencies and nonlinearities in the QoE dynamics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.MM (Multimedia), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
